We're outside, and we're telling children to go outside there is as principal demos talked about sometimes the feasibility of how prepared students are, but a lot of that is handled on a case by case basis.

390
00:42:37,373 --> 00:42:38,514
I do want to say.

391
00:42:41,682 --> 00:42:50,987
The elementary schools are responsive classroom schools, and the tenant of responsive classroom is about logical consequences.

392
00:42:51,668 --> 00:43:00,553
So I do, which means that recess should not be used as a punishment.

393
00:43:01,033 --> 00:43:09,158
However, if we do have unsafe behaviors in schools, our job is to educate children around

394
00:43:11,157 --> 00:43:15,578
pro-social behaviors and the safety of being around their peers.

395
00:43:15,998 --> 00:43:24,940
And so sometimes if they're exhibiting that, especially during play, the logical consequence is that they're removed from that.

396
00:43:25,380 --> 00:43:26,480
They're still outside.

397
00:43:26,580 --> 00:43:28,060
There may be a reflective moment.

398
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:29,441
There may be a walking moment.

399
00:43:30,001 --> 00:43:36,242
The element of child directed may be skewed because that's the logical consequence for the action.

400
00:43:37,242 --> 00:43:41,584
I don't know of it being used for anything other than that.

401
00:43:42,304 --> 00:43:49,006
If there are those like one off situations I would, I would really welcome a conversation about that.

402
00:43:51,312 --> 00:44:09,946
But I just wanted to kind of capture the piece of the responsive classroom being around what's logical, because that's how children, especially the elementary level, make connections around their behavior, is when the consequences are logical to what the behavior was.

403
00:44:13,169 --> 00:44:13,409
Thanks.

404
00:44:13,829 --> 00:44:14,109
