596
01:06:16,764 --> 01:06:22,287
One thing that I would do is I would ask those probing questions of, have you spoken with the classroom teacher?

597
01:06:22,327 --> 01:06:24,448
Have you talked to the principal?

598
01:06:24,588 --> 01:06:25,929
And did you get anywhere from there?

599
01:06:26,709 --> 01:06:28,130
And then send them back to that.

600
01:06:28,270 --> 01:06:33,413
I would then send an email to the principal and say, I just want to let you know that, you know,

601
01:06:34,253 --> 01:06:44,015
So and so is in requesting some information in regards to recess, could you please reach out to them and then let me know when that's been handled, then I would reach out to the family and just say.

602
01:06:44,512 --> 01:06:48,915
had you had a successful conversation and kind of follow it up that way.

603
01:06:49,276 --> 01:06:54,980
But I definitely think that when you said that chattering the course comment, it brought me back to that.

604
01:06:55,040 --> 01:06:57,922
And I understand that that is a really hard place to be at.

605
01:06:58,362 --> 01:07:03,987
But as a sitting principal now and with my school committee hat off, I totally appreciate that communication coming back.

606
01:07:04,047 --> 01:07:07,509
And I don't mind if you just send an email or call that says, hey, by the way,

607
01:07:09,010 --> 01:07:16,415
I'm hearing from so-and-so about recess because I'm knocking on wood right now, but it isn't a topic that I hear from many families.

608
01:07:16,455 --> 01:07:24,981
So if you're getting emails and calls on your level that I can't help them at the building level, then I feel sort of bad about that because if I know I can help.

609
01:07:25,481 --> 01:07:28,503
So I do just appreciate you listening to that comment.

610
01:07:28,543 --> 01:07:28,883
